author: @datasciyinfo5133
text: At first I thought this was exactly what I was looking for, but actually it doesn't show the true speed of Colab (Pro or free).  He never showed even one clip of the time on running epochs on the Colab side, just that the Laptop side took 4s 209 ms/epoch.  And the example had very few images as far as deep learning tasks go, so it would not have taxed even a low-budget CPU laptop.  Tesla P100 depends on bandwidth speed from the user to the server AND from google drive to colab gpu server.  Images should definitely have been uploaded directly to the Colab server before loading.  Still, the delay is far too long on the colab side.  I assume it is because of very slow internet connection from the user to Colab servers.  It's OK as a concept video to show that you CAN do deep learning on a RTX 3060 laptop.
